<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-746-524  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 746 524.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>MacWEEK  August 14 1990 v4 n28 p4(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Coastal Associates Publishing L.P. 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Shortcut simplifies file management, navigation. (Aladdin SystemsInc. introduces Shortcut 1.5 disk management and navigationutility) (product announcement)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Norr, Henry.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   Aladdin Systems Inc. (product introduction).andO;Product:   ShortCut 1.5 (File management software) (product introduction).andO;Topic:     File ManagementSearchingDisk-Tape File UtilitiesProduct Introduction.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>By Henry NorrandM;Boston -- Aladdin Systems Inc. last week announced Shortcut 1.5, an enhancedversion of its disk-management and navigation utility.andM;The $79.95 Startup document (INIT) adds a pop-up menu to Open and Savedialogs that helps users find missing files; rename, delete and lock files;decompress archives created with Aladdin's StuffIt; and jump quickly toregularly visited locations in their folder hierarchies.andP;  Due next month, thenew version will:andM;andgt;Present StuffIt archives in dialog boxes' list windows as if they werefolders.andP;  Opening the pseudo-folder and double-clicking on a document willautomatically decompress and open it.andM;andgt;&quot;Remember&quot; recently opened files and folders, so users can return to themquickly by choosing them from a Shortcut menu.andM;andgt;Have a View command that lets users open, copy and print text and PICTdocuments from within the dialog boxes of any application, even programs thatdon't normally open such documents.andP;  For example, Aladdin said, the featurewill make it easier for users to paste PICT images into their word processingdocuments or text into drawings.andM;Upgrades will be sent free to registered users, Aladdin said.andM;Aladdin Systems Inc. is located at Deer Park Center, Suite 23A-171, Aptos,Calif.andP;  95003; (408) 685-9175.andO;</TEXT></DOC>